  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking an experienced and dedicated <strong>Construction Project Manager</strong> to oversee construction projects from inception to completion on a <strong>long-term basis</strong>. The ideal candidate will be responsible for ensuring that projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to the specified quality standards, while maintaining a safe and productive work environment.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Plan, coordinate, and manage all phases of construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with architects, engineers, subcontractors, and vendors.</li>\n  <li>Create and manage detailed project schedules and budgets.</li>\n  <li>Monitor project progress and prepare regular reports for stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with safety regulations and company policies.</li>\n  <li>Manage procurement of materials and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Resolve any issues or conflicts that arise during construction.</li>\n  <li>Supervise site personnel and subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Conduct site inspections to ensure quality and safety standards are met.</li>\n  <li>Oversee project close-out, including punch lists, inspections, and documentation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Qualifications </h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum of 15+ years of experience in construction project management.</li>\n  <li>Proven track record of managing residential, commercial, or infrastructure projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of construction methods, materials, and legal regulations.</li>\n  <li>Excellent leadership, communication, and organizational skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and manage multiple projects simultaneously.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Additional Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Willingness to commit to a long-term working relationship.</li>\n  <li>Ability to travel to project sites as required.</li>\n  <li>Must possess a valid driver’s license and reliable transportation.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 12,
